IGcomment: Standardized or dictionary-derived text description of SUTRT or SUMODIFY if the sponsor chooses to code the substance use. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes.

label: Category for Substance Use
IGcomment: Used to define a category of related records. Examples: TOBACCO, ALCOHOL, or CAFFEINE.

label: Subcategory for Substance Use
IGcomment: A further categorization of substance use. Examples: CIGARS, CIGARETTES, BEER, WINE

label: SU Pre-Specified
IGcomment: Used to indicate whether (Y/null) information about the use of a specific substance was solicited on the CRF.

label: SU Occurrence
IGcomment: When the use of specific substances is solicited, SUOCCUR is used to indicate whether or not (Y/N) a particular pre-specified substance was used. Values are null for substances not specifically solicited.

label: Completion Status
algorithm: Set to NOT DONE if 'ND', 'NA', 'NK' ,' ' have been reported on CRF
IGcomment: When the use of pre-specified substances is solicited, the completion status indicates that there was no response to the question about the pre-specified substance. When there is no pre-specified list on the CRF, then the completion status indicates that substance use was not assessed for the subject.

label: Reason Substance Use Not Collected
IGcomment: Describes the reason substance use was not collected. Used in conjunction with SUSTAT when value of SUSTAT is NOT DONE.

label: Substance Use Class
IGcomment: Substance use class. May be obtained from coding. When coding to a single class, populate with class value. If using a dictionary and coding to multiple classes, then follow Section 4: 4.1.2.8.3, Multiple Values For A Non-Result Qualifier Variable or omit SUCLAS.

label: Substance Use Class Code
IGcomment: Code corresponding to SUCLAS. May be obtained from coding.

label: Substance Use Consumption
IGcomment: Amount of SUTRT consumed. Not populated if SUDOSTXT is populated.

label: Substance Use Consumption Text
IGcomment: Substance use consumption amounts or a range of consumption information collected in text form. Not populated if SUDOSE is populated.

label: Consumption Units
IGcomment: Units for SUDOSE, SUDOSTOT, or SUDOSTXT. Examples: OUNCES, CIGARETTE EQUIVALENTS, GRAMS.

label: Dose Form
IGcomment: Dose form for SUTRT. Examples: INJECTABLE, LIQUID, or POWDER.

label: Use Frequency Per Interval
IGcomment: Usually expressed as the number of repeated administrations of SUDOSE within a specific time period. Example: Q24H (every day)

label: Total Daily Consumption
IGcomment: Total daily use of SUTRT using the units in SUDOSU. Used when dosing is collected as Total Daily Dose. If sponsor needs to aggregate the data over a period other than daily, then the aggregated total could be recorded in a Supplemental Qualifier variable.

label: Route of Administration
IGcomment: Route of administration for SUTRT. Examples: ORAL, INTRAVENOUS.

label: Element Code
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: The name of the Element.

label: Visit Number
comment: Multiple unscheduled visits or non-visits can exist having the same visit ID but with different dates. This might result in duplicate records for the same visit number but with different dates

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
comment: Based on TV.VISITDY

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. (See Section 3.2.2).

label: Date/Time of Collection
comment: Assigned to date of visit

label: Study Day of Visit/Collection/Exam
algorithm: Calculation: = SUDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if SUDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,SUDTC - RFSTDTC if SUDTC precedes RFSTDTC

label: Study Day of Start of Substance Use
algorithm: Calculation: = SUSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if SUSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,SUSTDTC - RFSTDTC if SUSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of start of substance use relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

label: Study Day of End of Substance Use
algorithm: Calculation: = SUENDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if SUENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,SUENDTC - RFSTDTC if SUENDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of end of substance use relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

label: Duration of Substance Use
IGcomment: Collected duration of substance use in ISO 8601 format. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and -- TPTREF.

label: Planned Time Point Number
IGcomment: Numeric version of planned time point used in sorting.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

label: Time Point Reference
IGcomment: Description of the fixed reference point referred to by --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Start Relative to Reference Period
algorithm: Classifies the start of the medication relative to reference period as defined by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics.
IGcomment: Describes the start of the substance use relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as "PRIOR", "ONGOING", or "CONTINUING" was collected, this information may be translated into SUSTRF. This variable is proposed for deletion post SDTM V1.4.

label: End Relative to Reference Period
algorithm: Classifies the end of the medication relative to reference period as defined by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics. If reported as ongoing on the CRF, the value will be set to ONGOING.
IGcomment: Describes the end of the substance use with relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as "PRIOR", "ONGOING", or "CONTINUING" was collected, this information may be translated into SUENRF. This variable is proposed for deletion post SDTM V1.4.

label: Start Relative to Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Identifies the start of the substance as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable SUSTTPT.

label: Start Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by SUSTRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-15" or "VISIT 1".

label: End Relative to Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Identifies the end of the substance as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable SUENTPT.

label: End Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by SUENRTPT. Examples: "2003-12-25" or "VISIT 2".

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Unique Subject Identifier
comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

label: Group ID
IGcomment: Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. Also used to link together a block of related records in the Trial Summary dataset (Section 3.4).

label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
comment: System generated unique identifier, can be used as reference to the ADaM domains
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined identifier. Example: pre-printed line identifier on a Concomitant Medications page.

label: Visit Number
IGcomment: 1. Clinical encounter number. (Decimal numbering may be useful for inserting unplanned visits.) 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

label: Visit Name
IGcomment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY as a text description of the clinical encounter.

label: Epi/Pandemic Related Change Indicator
algorithm: Derived based on SVCNTMOD, SVGRPID and/or related record in CO domain

label: Element Code
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: The name of the Element.

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
comment: Based on TV.VISITDY
IGcomment: Planned study day of the start of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. (See Section 3.2.2).

label: Start Date/Time of Visit
IGcomment: Start date/time for a Visit.

label: End Date/Time of Visit
comment: Same as SVSTDTC
IGcomment: End date/time of a Visit.

label: Study Day of Start of Visit
algorithm: Calculation: = SVSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if SVSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,SVSTDTC - RFSTDTC if SVSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of start of visit relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

label: Study Day of End of Visit
algorithm: Calculation: = SVENDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if SVENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,SVENDTC - RFSTDTC if SVENDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of end of visit relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.

label: Description of Unplanned Visit
IGcomment: Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned visit.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Planned Arm Code
IGcomment: ARMCD is limited to 20 characters and does not have special character restrictions. The maximum length of ARMCD is longer than that for other "short" variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. For example, if ARMCD values for a seven-period crossover were constructed using two-character abbreviations for each treatment and separating hyphens, the length of ARMCD values would be 20.

label: Description of Planned Arm
IGcomment: Name given to an Arm or treatment group.

label: Planned Order of Element within Arm
IGcomment: Number that gives the order of the Element within the Arm.

label: Element Code
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
IGcomment: The name of the Element. The same Element may occur more than once within an Arm.

label: Branch
IGcomment: Condition subject met, at a "branch" in the trial design at the end of this Element, to be included in this Arm; (e.g., randomization to DRUG X).

label: Transition Rule
IGcomment: If the trial design allows a subject to transition to an Element other than the next Element in sequence, then the conditions for transitioning to those other Elements, and the alternative Element sequences, are specified in this rule (e.g., Responders go to washout).

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Name of the Trial Epoch with which this Element of the Arm is associated.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Sequence of Planned Assessment Schedule
IGcomment: A number given to ensure ordinal sequencing of the planned assessment schedules within a trial.

label: Anchor Variable Name
IGcomment: A reference to the date variable name that provides the start point from which the planned disease assessment schedule is measured. This must be a referenced from the ADaM ADSL dataset e.g. ANCH1DT. Note: TDANCVAR will contain the name of a reference date variable.

label: Offset from the Anchor
IGcomment: A fixed offset from the date provided by the variable referenced in TDANCVAR. This is used when the timing of planned cycles does not start on the exact day referenced in the variable indicated in TDANCVAR. The value of this variable will be either zero or a positive value and will be represented in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Planned Assessment Interval
IGcomment: The planned interval between disease assessments represented in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Planned Assessment Interval Minimum
IGcomment: The lower limit of the allowed range for the planned interval between disease assessments represented in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Planned Assessment Interval Maximum
IGcomment: The upper limit of the allowed range for the planned interval between disease assessments represented in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Maximum Number of Actual Assessments
IGcomment: This variable must represent the maximum number of actual assessments for the analysis that this disease assessment schedule describes. In a trial where the maximum number of assessments is not defined explicitly in the protocol (e.g. assessments occur until death) TDNUMRPT should represent the maximum number of disease assessments that support the efficacy analysis, encountered by any subject across the trial at that point in time.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Element Code
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
IGcomment: The name of the Element.

label: Rule for Start of Element
IGcomment: Expresses rule for beginning Element.

label: Rule for End of Element
IGcomment: Expresses rule for ending Element. Either TEENRL or TEDUR must be present for each Element.

label: Planned Duration of Element
IGcomment: Planned Duration of Element in ISO 8601 format. Used when the rule for ending the Element is applied after a fixed duration.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Incl/Excl Criterion Short Name
IGcomment: Short name IETEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in IETESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., "1TEST"). IETESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. The prefix "IE" is used to ensure consistency with the IE domain.

label: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion
IGcomment: Full text of the inclusion or exclusion criterion. The prefix "IE" is used to ensure consistency with the IE domain.

label: Inclusion/Exclusion Category
IGcomment: Used for categorization of the inclusion or exclusion criteria.

label: Inclusion/Exclusion Subcategory
IGcomment: A further categorization of the exception criterion. Can be used to distinguish criteria for a sub-study or for to categorize as a major or minor exceptions. Examples: MAJOR, MINOR.

label: Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Rule
IGcomment: Rule that expresses the criterion in computer-executable form (see assumption 4 below).

label: Protocol Criteria Versions
IGcomment: The number of this version of the Inclusion/Exclusion criteria. May be omitted if there is only one version.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Unique Subject Identifier
comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

label: Sponsor Device Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined identifier for a device

label: Sequence Number
algorithm: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID
IGcomment: Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness within a dataset for a subject. May be any valid number.

label: Group ID
IGcomment: Used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain.

label: Reference ID
IGcomment: Internal or external identifier.

label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined identifier.

label: Link ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link the assessment result records to the individual tumor identification record in TU domain.

label: Link Group
IGcomment: Used to group and link all of the measurement/assessment records used in the assessment of the response record in the RS domain.

label: Tumor Assessment Short Name
IGcomment: Short name of the TEST in TRTEST. TRTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: TUMSTATE, DIAMETER. See Assumption 2.

label: Tumor Assessment Test Name
IGcomment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in TRTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Tumor State, Diameter, Longest Perpendicular diameter, Volume, Area. See Assumption 2.

label: Result or Finding in Original Units
IGcomment: Result of the Tumor measurement/assessment as originally received or collected.

label: Original Units
IGcomment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for TRORRES. Example: mm

label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format
IGcomment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from TRORRES in a standard format or standard units. TRSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in TRSTRESN

label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units
IGcomment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from TRSTRESC. TRSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

label: Standard Units
IGcomment: Standardized unit used for TRSTRESN.

label: Completion Status
algorithm: Set to NOT DONE if 'ND', 'NA', 'NK' ,' ' have been reported on CRF
IGcomment: Used to indicate a scan/image/physical exam was not performed or a tumor measurement was not taken. Should be Null if a result exists in TRORRES.

label: Reason Tumor Measurement Not Performed
IGcomment: Describes why a scan/image/physical exam was not performed or a tumor measurement was not taken. Examples: SCAN NOT PERFORMED, NOT ASSESSABLE: Image obscured, TUMOR. Used in conjunction with TRSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

label: Vendor Name
IGcomment: The name or identifier of the vendor that performed the Tumor measurement or assessment. This column can be left Null when the Investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain.

label: Method used to Identify the Tumor
IGcomment: Method used to measure the tumor. Examples: MRI, CT SCAN.

label: Evaluator
IGcomment: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Examples: INVESTIGATOR, INDEPENDENT ASSESSOR. This column can be left Null when the Investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain. However the column should contain no Null values when data from one or more independent assessors is included meaning that the rows attributed to the Investigator should contain a value of INVESTIGATOR.

label: Evaluator Identifier
IGcomment: The Evaluator Specified variable is used in conjunction with TREVAL to provide an additional level of detail. When multiple assessors play the role identified in TREVAL, values of TREVALID will attribute a row of data to a particular assessor. TREVALID should not contain the names of the assessors, or a code identifier for a specific assessor, but should contain values such as RADIOLOGIST, RADIOLOGIST 1 or RADIOLOGIST 2. The TREVALID variable is subject to CDISC Controlled Terminology. Note TREVAL must also be populated when TREVALID is populated. See Assumption 7.

label: Accepted Record Flag
IGcomment: In cases where more than one independent assessor (e.g. RADIOLOGIST 1, RADIOLOGIST 2, ADJUDICATOR) provide independent assessments at the same timepoint this flag identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment.

label: Repetition Number
IGcomment: The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary, e.g., within a time point or within a visit. For example, multiple measurements of blood pressure or multiple analyses of a sample.

label: Element Code
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: The name of the Element.

IGcomment: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

label: Visit Name
IGcomment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

comment: Based on TV.VISITDY

comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Epoch associated with the Element in the planned sequence of Elements for the ARM to which the subject was assigned

IGcomment: TRDTC variable represents the date of the scan/image/physical exam not the date that the image was read to identify tumors. TRDTC variable does not represent the VISIT date.

label: Study Day of Tumor Measurement
algorithm: Calculation: = TRDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if TRDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,TRDTC - RFSTDTC if TRDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: 1. Study day of the scan/image/physical exam, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and -- TPTREF.

label: Planned Time Point Number
IGcomment: Numeric version of planned time point used in sorting.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

label: Time Point Reference
IGcomment: Description of the fixed reference point referred to by --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Sequence Number
algorithm: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID
IGcomment: Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness within a dataset. Allows inclusion of multiple records for the same TSPARMCD, and can be used to join related records.

label: Group ID
IGcomment: Used to tie together a group of related records

label: Trial Summary Parameter Short Name
IGcomment: TSPARMCD (the companion to TSPARM) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that TSPARMCD will need to serve as variable names. Examples: AGEMIN, AGEMAX

label: Trial Summary Parameter
IGcomment: Term for the Trial Summary Parameter. The value in TSPARM cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples Planned Minimum Age of Subjects, Planned Maximum Age of Subjects

label: Parameter Value
IGcomment: Value of TSPARM. Example: "ASTHMA" when TSPARM value is "Trial Indication". TSVAL can only be null when TSVALNF is populated. Text over 200 characters can be added to additional columns TSVAL1-TSVALn.

label: Parameter Null Flavor
IGcomment: Null flavor for the value of TSPARM, to be populated if and only if TSVAL is null.

label: Parameter Value Code
IGcomment: This is the code of the term in TSVAL. For example; 6CW7F3G59X is the code for Gabapentin, C49488 is the code for Y. The length of this variable can be longer than 8 to accommodate the length of the external terminology.

label: Name of the Reference Terminology
IGcomment: The name of the Reference Terminology from which TSVALCD is taken. For example; CDISC, SNOMED, ISO 8601.

label: Version of the Reference Terminology
IGcomment: The version number of the Reference Terminology, if applicable.

comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined identifier.

label: Link Group ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link related records across domains. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. For example: Multiple tumor measurements/assessments will contribute to a single response to therapy determination record.

label: Tumor Identification Short Name
IGcomment: Short name of the TEST in TUTEST. TUTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters nor can start with a number. TUTESTCD contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Example: TUMIDENT (Tumor Identification). See Assumption 2.

label: Tumor Identification Test Name
IGcomment: Verbatim name of the test for the tumor identification. The value in TUTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Example: Tumor Identification. See Assumption 2.

label: Tumor Identification Result
IGcomment: Result of the Tumor identification. The result of tumor identification is a classification of identified tumor. Examples: When TUTESTCD=TUMIDENT (Tumor Identification), values of TUORRES might be: TARGET, NON-TARGET, or NEW. or BENIGN ABNORMALITY

label: Tumor Identification Result Std. Format
IGcomment: Contains the result value for all findings copied from TUORRES.

label: Vendor Name
IGcomment: The name or identifier of the vendor that performed the Tumor Identification. This column can be left Null when the Investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain.

label: Location of the Tumor
IGcomment: Used to specify the anatomical location of the identified tumor. Example: LIVER Note: When anatomical location is broken down and collected as distinct pieces of data that when combined provide the overall location information (e.g. laterality /directionality / distribution) then the additional anatomical location qualifiers should be used. See Assumption 3.

label: Laterality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing laterality, for example, LEFT, RIGHT, BILATERAL.

label: Directionality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing directionality, for example, UPPER, INTERIOR.

label: Portion or Totality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing the distribution which means arrangement of, or apportioning of, for example, ENTIRE, SINGLE, SEGMENT, MULTIPLE.

label: Method of Identification
IGcomment: Method used to identify the tumor. Examples: MRI, CT SCAN.

label: Evaluator
IGcomment: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Examples: INVESTIGATOR, INDEPENDNT ASSESSOR This column can be left Null when the Investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain. However the column should contain no Null values when data from one or more independent assessors is included meaning that the rows attributed to the Investigator should contain a value of INVESTIGATOR.

TUEVALID should not contain the names of the assessors, or a code identifier for a specific assessor, but should contain values such as RADIOLOGIST, RADIOLOGIST 1 or RADIOLOGIST 2. The TUEVALID variable is subject to CDISC Controlled Terminology. See Assumption 7.

label: Accepted Record Flag
IGcomment: In cases where more than one independent assessor (e.g. RADIOLOGIST 1, RADIOLOGIST 2, ADJUDICATOR) provide independent assessments at the same time point this flag identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment.

label: Repetition Number
IGcomment: The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary, e.g., within a time point or within a visit. For example, multiple measurements of blood pressure or multiple analyses of a sample.

comment: Set based on the SE domain

algorithm: Calculation: = TUDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if TUDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,TUDTC - RFSTDTC if TUDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: 1. Study day of the scan/image/physical exam, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and -- TPTREF.

label: Planned Time Point Number
IGcomment: Numeric version of planned time point used in sorting.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

label: Time Point Reference
IGcomment: Description of the fixed reference point referred to by --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain

label: Visit Number
IGcomment: 1. Clinical encounter number 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

label: Visit Name
IGcomment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY as a text description of the clinical encounter.

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
IGcomment: 1. Planned study day of VISIT. 2. Due to its sequential nature, used for sorting.

label: Planned Arm Code
IGcomment: 1.ARMCD is limited to 20 characters and does not have special character restrictions. The maximum length of ARMCD is longer than for other "short" variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. For example, if ARMCD values for a seven- period crossover were constructed using two-character abbreviations for each treatment and separating hyphens, the length of ARMCD values would be 20. 2. If the timing of Visits for a trial does not depend on which ARM a subject is in, then ARMCD should be null.

label: Description of Planned Arm
IGcomment: 1. Name given to an Arm or Treatment Group. 2. If the timing of Visits for a trial does not depend on which Arm a subject is in, then Arm should be left blank.

label: Visit Start Rule
IGcomment: Rule describing when the Visit starts, in relation to the sequence of Elements.

label: Visit End Rule
IGcomment: Rule describing when the Visit ends, in relation to the sequence of Elements.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Unique Subject Identifier
comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

label: Sponsor Device Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined identifier for a device

label: Sequence Number
algorithm: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID
IGcomment: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

label: Group ID
IGcomment: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database.

label: Link ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link related records across domains. This may be a one-to- one or a one-to-many relationship. For Example: A single tumor may have multiple measurements/assessments performed at each study visit.

label: Link Group ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link related records across domains. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. For example: Multiple tumor measurements/assessments will contribute to a single response to therapy determination record.

label: Vital Signs Test Short Name
IGcomment: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in VSTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in VSTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g."1TEST"). VSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: SYSBP, DIABP, BMI.

label: Vital Signs Test Name
IGcomment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in VSTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Systolic Blood Pressure, Diastolic Blood Pressure, Body Mass Index.

label: Category for Vital Signs
IGcomment: Used to define a category of related records.

label: Subcategory for Vital Signs
IGcomment: A further categorization of a measurement or examination.

label: Vital Signs Position of Subject
IGcomment: Position of the subject during a measurement or examination. Examples: SUPINE, STANDING, SITTING.

label: Result or Finding in Original Units
IGcomment: Result of the vital signs measurement as originally received or collected.

label: Original Units
IGcomment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for VSORRES. Examples: IN, LB, BEATS/MIN.

label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format
algorithm: VSORRES converted into standard unit
IGcomment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from VSORRES in a standard format or standard units. VSSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in VSSTRESN. For example, if a test has results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in VSORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in VSSTRESC as "NEGATIVE".

label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units
algorithm: VSORRES converted into standard unit
IGcomment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from VSSTRESC. VSSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

label: Standard Units
IGcomment: Standardized unit used for VSSTRESC and VSSTRESN.

label: Completion Status
algorithm: Set to NOT DONE if 'ND', 'NA', 'NK' ,' ' have been reported on CRF
IGcomment: Used to indicate that a vital sign measurement was not done. Should be null if a result exists in VSORRES.

label: Reason Not Performed
algorithm: Set to NOT COLLECTED if VSSTAT is set to NOT DONE
IGcomment: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Examples: BROKEN EQUIPMENT or SUBJECT REFUSED. Used in conjunction with VSSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

label: Location of Vital Signs Measurement
IGcomment: Location relevant to the collection of Vital Signs measurement. Example: ARM for blood pressure.

label: Laterality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing laterality. Examples: RIGHT, LEFT, BILATERAL

label: Method of Test or Examination
IGcomment: Method of the test or examination. Examples: EIA (Enzyme Immunoassay), ELECTROPHORESIS, DIPSTICK

label: Baseline Flag
algorithm: Baseline flag set to Y when the assessment is collected at the visit marked as baseline in the trial flowchart
IGcomment: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be "Y" or null.

label: Derived Flag
IGcomment: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records which represent the average of other records or which do not come from the CRF are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If VSDRVFL=Y, then VSORRES may be null, with VSSTRESC and (if numeric) VSSTRESN having the derived value.

label: Evaluator
IGcomment: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Examples: ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE, INDEPENDENT ASSESSOR, RADIOLOGIST.

label: Evaluator Identifier
IGcomment: Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in --EVAL. Examples: RADIOLOGIST1 or RADIOLOGIST2

label: Repetition Number
IGcomment: The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary, e.g., within a time point or within a visit. For example, multiple measurements of blood pressure or multiple analyses of a sample.

comment: Set based on the SE domain

IGcomment: Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. IGcomment: Identifier used to link related records across domains. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. For example: Multiple tumor measurements/assessments will contribute to a single response to therapy determination record.

label: Findings About Test Short Name
comment: Assigned in mapping or terminology conversion
IGcomment: Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in FATEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in FATESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g. "1TEST"). FATESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Example: SEV, OCCUR.

label: Findings About Test Name
comment: Assigned in mapping or terminology conversion
IGcomment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in FATEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Severity/Intensity, Occurrence

label: Object of the Observation
comment: Type of event
IGcomment: Used to describe the object or focal point of the findings observation that is represented by --TEST. Examples: the term (such as Acne) describing a clinical sign or symptom that is being measured by a Severity test, or an event such as VOMIT where the volume of Vomit is being measured by a VOLUME test.

label: Category for Findings About
IGcomment: Used to define a category of related records. Examples: GERD, PRE-SPECIFIED AE.

label: Subcategory for Findings About
IGcomment: A further categorization of FACAT.

label: Result or Finding in Original Units
IGcomment: Result of the test as originally received or collected.

label: Original Units
IGcomment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for FAORRES.

label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format
IGcomment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from FAORRES in a standard format or standard units. FASTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in FASTRESN. For example, if a test has results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in FAORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning; they could be represented in standard format in FASTRESC as "NEGATIVE".

label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units
IGcomment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from FASTRESC. FASTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

label: Standard Units
IGcomment: Standardized unit used for FASTRESC and FASTRESN.

label: Completion Status
algorithm: Set to NOT DONE if 'ND', 'NA', 'NK' ,' ' have been reported on CRF
IGcomment: Used to indicate that the measurement was not done. Should be null if a result exists in FAORRES.

label: Reason Not Performed
algorithm: Set to NOT COLLECTED if ZASTAT is set to NOT DONE
IGcomment: Describes why a question was not answered. Example: subject refused. Used in conjunction with FASTAT when value is NOT DONE.

label: Location of the Finding About
IGcomment: Used to specify the location of the clinical evaluation. Example: ARM

label: Laterality of Location of Finding About
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location or specimen further detailing laterality. Examples: RIGHT, LEFT, BILATERAL

label: Baseline Flag
algorithm: Baseline flag set to Y when the assessment is collected at the visit marked as baseline in the trial flowchart
IGcomment: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be "Y" or null.

label: Vendor Name
IGcomment: Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provided the test results.

label: Evaluator
IGcomment: Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Should be null for records that contain collected or derived data. Examples: INVESTIGATOR, ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE, VENDOR.

label: Evaluator Identifier
comment: The level at which the adjudication result is reached
IGcomment: Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in --EVAL. Examples: RADIOLOGIST1 or RADIOLOGIST2

label: Element Code
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name.

label: Description of Element
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: The name of the Element.

label: Visit Number
IGcomment: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

label: Visit Name
IGcomment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
comment: Based on TV.VISITDY
IGcomment: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. (See Section 3.2.2).

label: Study Day of Collection
algorithm: Calculation: = ZADTC - RFSTDTC+1 if ZADTC is on or after RFSTDTC,ZADTC - RFSTDTC if ZADTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: 1. Study day of collection, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See --TPTNUM and -- TPTREF.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned Elapsed time in ISO 8601 character format relative to a planned fixed reference (--TPTREF) such as "Previous Dose" or "Previous Meal". This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Study Identifier
IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Unique Subject Identifier
comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

label: Sequence Number
algorithm: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID
IGcomment: Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

label: Group ID
IGcomment: Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject.

label: Reference ID
IGcomment: Internal or external identifier (e.g., kit number, bottle label, vial identifier).

label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier
IGcomment: Sponsor-defined reference number. Perhaps pre-printed on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on a CRF Page.

label: Link ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link related records across domains.

label: Link Group ID
IGcomment: Identifier used to link related, grouped records across domains.

label: Name of Treatment
IGcomment: Name of the intervention treatment known to the subject and/or administrator.

label: Mood
IGcomment: Mode or condition of the record specifying whether the intervention (activity) is intended to happen or has happened. Values align with BRIDG pillars (e.g., scheduled context, performed context) and HL7 activity moods (e.g., intent, event). Examples: SCHEDULED, PERFORMED. CDISC Controlled Terminology request for MOOD codelist with values of SCHEDULED and PERFORMED has been submitted.

label: Category of Treatment
IGcomment: Used to define a category of related ECTRT values.

label: Subcategory of Treatment
IGcomment: A further categorization of ECCAT values.

label: Pre-Specified
IGcomment: Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified. Values should be "Y" or null.

label: Occurrence
IGcomment: Used to indicate whether a treatment occurred when information about the occurrence is solicited. ECOCCUR = 'N' when a treatment was not taken, not given, or missed.

label: Dose
IGcomment: Amount of ECTRT when numeric. Not populated when ECDOSTXT is populated.

label: Dose Description
IGcomment: Amount of ECTRT when non-numeric. Dosing amounts or a range of dosing information collected in text form. Example: 200-400. Not populated when ECDOSE is populated.

label: Dose Units
IGcomment: Units for ECDOSE, ECDOSTOT, or ECDOSTXT.

label: Dose Form
IGcomment: Dose form for ECTRT. Examples: TABLET, LOTION.

label: Dosing Frequency per Interval
IGcomment: Usually expressed as the number of repeated administrations of ECDOSE within a specific time period. Examples: Q2H, QD, BID.

label: Total Daily Dose
IGcomment: Total daily dose of ECTRT using the units in ECDOSU. Used when dosing is collected as Total Daily Dose.

label: Intended Dose Regimen
IGcomment: Text description of the intended schedule or regimen for the Intervention. Example: TWO WEEKS ON, TWO WEEKS OFF.

label: Route of Administration
IGcomment: Route of administration for the intervention. Examples: ORAL, INTRAVENOUS.

label: Lot Number
IGcomment: Lot Number of the ECTRT product.

label: Location of Dose Administration
IGcomment: Specifies location of administration. Example: ARM, LIP.

label: Laterality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location further detailing laterality of the intervention administration. Examples: LEFT, RIGHT.

label: Directionality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location further detailing directionality. Examples: ANTERIOR, LOWER, PROXIMAL, UPPER.

label: Portion or Totality
IGcomment: Qualifier for anatomical location further detailing distribution, which means arrangement of, apportioning of. Examples: ENTIRE, SINGLE, SEGMENT.

label: Fasting Status
IGcomment: Indicator used to identify fasting status. Examples: Y, N.

label: Pharmaceutical Strength
IGcomment: Amount of an active ingredient expressed quantitatively per dosage unit, per unit of volume, or per unit of weight, according to the pharmaceutical dose form.

label: Pharmaceutical Strength Units
IGcomment: Unit for ECPSTRG. Examples: mg/TABLET, mg/mL.

label: Reason for Dose Adjustment
IGcomment: Describes reason or explanation of why a dose is adjusted.

comment: Set based on the SE domain

comment: Set based on the SE domain

comment: Multiple unscheduled visits or non-visits can exist having the same visit ID but with different dates. This might result in duplicate records for the same visit number but with different dates

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
comment: Based on TV.VISITDY

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Trial Epoch of the exposure as collected record. Examples: RUN-IN, TREATMENT.

label: Start Date/Time of Treatment
IGcomment: The date/time when administration of the treatment indicated by ECTRT and ECDOSE began.

label: End Date/Time of Treatment
IGcomment: The date/time when administration of the treatment indicated by ECTRT and ECDOSE ended. For administrations considered given at a point in time (e.g., oral tablet, pre-filled syringe injection), where only an administration date/time is collected, ECSTDTC should be copied to ECENDTC as the standard representation.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by ECTPTREF in ISO 8601 character format.

label: Study Day of Start of Treatment
algorithm: Calculation: = ECSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if ECSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,ECSTDTC - RFSTDTC if ECSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of ECSTDTC relative to the sponsor-defined DM.RFSTDTC.

label: Study Day of End of Treatment
algorithm: Calculation: = ZEENDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if ZEENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,ZEENDTC - RFSTDTC if ZEENDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: Study day of ECENDTC relative to the sponsor-defined DM.RFSTDTC.

label: Duration of Treatment
IGcomment: Collected duration of administration represented in ISO 8601 duration format. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: Text Description of time when administration should occur. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See ECTPTNUM and ECTPTREF.

label: Planned Time Point Number
IGcomment: Numerical version of ECTPT to aid in sorting.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601 format) relative to the planned fixed reference (ECTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time. Represented in ISO 8601 duration format.

label: Time Point Reference
IGcomment: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by ECELTM, ECTPTNUM, and ECTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

IGcomment: Unique identifier for a study.

label: Domain Abbreviation
IGcomment: Two-character abbreviation for the domain.

label: Unique Subject Identifier
comment: Concatenation of STUDYID and DM.SUBJID
IGcomment: Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product.

The value in LBTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g."1TEST"). LBTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: ALT, LDH.

label: Lab Test or Examination Name
IGcomment: Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. Note any test normally performed by a clinical laboratory is considered a lab test. The value in LBTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: Alanine Aminotransferase, Lactate Dehydrogenase.

label: Category for Lab Test
IGcomment: Used to define a category of related records across subjects. Examples: such as HEMATOLOGY, URINALYSIS, CHEMISTRY.

label: Subcategory for Lab Test
IGcomment: A further categorization of a test category such as DIFFERENTIAL, COAGULATON, LIVER FUNCTION, ELECTROLYTES.

IGcomment: Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected.

label: Original Units
IGcomment: Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for LBORRES. Example: g/L.

label: Reference Range Lower Limit in Orig Unit
IGcomment: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

label: Reference Range Upper Limit in Orig Unit
IGcomment: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format
algorithm: LBORRES converted into standard unit
IGcomment: Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from LBORRES in a standard format or standard units. LBSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in LBSTRESN. For example, if a test has results "NONE", "NEG", and "NEGATIVE" in LBORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in LBSTRESC as "NEGATIVE". For other examples, see general assumptions.

label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units
algorithm: LBORRES converted into standard unit
IGcomment: Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from LBSTRESC. LBSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings.

label: Standard Units
IGcomment: Standardized unit used for LBSTRESC or LBSTRESN.

label: Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units
algorithm: LBORNRLO converted to standard unit (LBSTRESU)
IGcomment: Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements for LBSTRESC/LBSTRESN in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

label: Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units
algorithm: LBORNRHI converted to standard unit (LBSTRESU)
IGcomment: Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results.

label: Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units
IGcomment: For normal range values that are character in ordinal scale or if categorical ranges were supplied (e.g., "-1 to +1", "NEGATIVE TO TRACE").

label: Reference Range Indicator
algorithm: If LBORRESN > LBORNRHI then LBNRIND=HIGH. If LBORRESN < LBORNRLO then LBNRIND=LOW. If LBORRESN between LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI then LBNRIND=NORMAL.
IGcomment: 1. Indicates where the value falls with respect to reference range defined by LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI, LBSTNRLO and LBSTNRHI, or by LBSTNRC. Examples: NORMAL, ABNORMAL, HIGH, LOW. 2. Sponsors should specify in the study metadata (Comments column in the define.xml) whether LBNRIND refers to the original or standard reference ranges and results. 3. Should not be used to indicate clinical significance.

algorithm: Set to NOT DONE if 'ND', 'NA', 'NK' ,' ' have been reported on CRF
IGcomment: Used to indicate exam not done. Should be null if a result exists in LBORRES.

IGcomment: Describes why a measurement or test was not performed such as BROKEN EQUIPMENT, SUBJECT REFUSED, or SPECIMEN LOST. Used in conjunction with LBSTAT when value is NOT DONE.

IGcomment: The name or identifier of the laboratory that performed the test.

IGcomment: 1. Dictionary-derived LOINC Code for LBTEST. 2. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes

label: Specimen Type
IGcomment: Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. Examples: SERUM, PLASMA, URINE.

label: Specimen Condition
IGcomment: Free or standardized text describing the condition of the specimen e.g. HEMOLYZED, ICTERIC, LIPEMIC etc.

label: Method of Test or Examination
IGcomment: Method of the test or examination. Examples: EIA (Enzyme Immunoassay), ELECTROPHORESIS, DIPSTICK

label: Analysis Method
IGcomment: Analysis method applied to obtain a summarized result. Analysis method describes the method of secondary processing applied to a complex observation result (e.g. an image or a genetic sequence).

algorithm: Baseline flag set to Y when the assessment is collected at the visit marked as baseline in the trial flowchart
IGcomment: Indicator used to identify a baseline value. The value should be "Y" or null.

label: Derived Flag
IGcomment: Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be Y or null. Records that represent the average of other records, or do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally received or collected are examples of records that might be derived for the submission datasets. If LBDRVFL=Y, then LBORRES may be null, with LBSTRESC, and (if numeric) LBSTRESN having the derived value.

The sponsor is expected to provide the name of the scale and version used to map the terms, utilizing the define.xml external codelist attributes.

IGcomment: Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in --EVAL. Examples: RADIOLOGIST1 or RADIOLOGIST2

IGcomment: The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary, e.g., within a time point or within a visit. For example, multiple measurements of blood pressure or multiple analyses of a sample.

label: Visit Number
IGcomment: 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.

label: Visit Name
IGcomment: 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.

label: Planned Study Day of Visit
comment: Based on TV.VISITDY
IGcomment: Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics.

label: Epoch
comment: Set based on the SE domain
IGcomment: Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. (See Section 3.2.2).

label: Study Day of Vital Signs
algorithm: Calculation: = VSDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if VSDTC is on or after RFSTDTC,VSDTC - RFSTDTC if VSDTC precedes RFSTDTC
IGcomment: 1. Study day of vital signs measurements, measured as integer days. 2. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics.

label: Planned Time Point Name
IGcomment: 1. Text Description of time when measurement should be taken. 2. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See VSTPTNUM and VSTPTREF. Examples: Start, 5 min post.

label: Planned Time Point Number
IGcomment: Numerical version of VSTPT to aid in sorting.

label: Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref
IGcomment: Planned Elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (VSTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable. Represented as an ISO 8601 Duration. Examples: "-PT15M" to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by VSTPTREF, or "PT8H" to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by VSTPTREF.

label: Time Point Reference
IGcomment: Name of the fixed reference point referred to by VSELTM, VSTPTNUM, and VSTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL.

label: Date/Time of Reference Time Point
IGcomment: Date/time of the reference time point, LBTPTREF.
